reviews.text: Reserved a table, yet we were told that none were available on arrival, had to wait 20min for one, ruined half the mood we had before we even had the first bite. To be fair, the food and drinks were pretty good. Loved the chicken scallopini and chicken tenders. Ribs could use some extra moisture though. The portions were also very fair.

This is one of the many in a chain of American grill restaurants  scattered about the territory. Famous for it's steaks. The decoration is standard to all branches.

Quality of food is quite good and so is the service but do feel that the pricing not necessarily equates to the quality of the food served. Yes would say the prices are on the high side. Pretty much standard quality.

Awful.  When I was still a kid it used to be a treat to eat at Dan Ryan’s.  We loved the ribs and the potato skins.  We went again today and everthing is just so ridiculously disappointing, especially when that bill was hefty.

Don’t go unless you have given up on life and you have so much money that you just want to get rid of some of it.
it is one of my favorite places where I can enjoy meeting friends and feel relaxed for having lunch or dinner

Thumb up for the warm hospitality, great service and wonderful food on my birthday at Dan Ryan restaurant. Complimentary birthday carrot cake and the crew of staffs sang the birthday song for me that shocked me. Thanks for the generosity of Dan Ryan, manager Christina Wong, and my two friends Christine and Elsa.

reviews.text: Good arcade to shop for medium to medium-high end brands in a spacious environment with both restaurants and food court to suit varying tastes of customers. Great parking lot. Multiple sakes receipts accepted for free parking.

Very crowded and very clean like a hospital. Come here on Sunday and you can enjoy waiting for a table for an hour with everyone. Best place if you want to buy a Rolex for $900,000 to go with your yacht sitting in a port in Italy.
Multiple restaurants and shops. A very big mall, and a nice theater to watch movies. The restaurants were also very nice. A very good shopping mall overall.

I like Festival Walk as it is rarely super crowded like the malls at Sha Tin always seem to be. The TASTE supermarket is fantastic here with a range of products from around the world including Waitrose products and a good frozen section. Other stores I like here are Zara Home, Log On, M&S and the Cinema which let's you bring Starbucks in. I sometimes come here to walk around on rainy days too as it is so big and there are very few shoppers with suitcases.

I like Windows shopping here.cause if not people mountain people sea. Can very relaxed to take a look.some shop I used take a look.like hk a female designer. She design Chinese match west.she control color very. Very good. Also one best of world shoe shop. Tecstoni.name may be not correct. It is one of best Italian designer band shoe shop.
